      "size": 4096,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-31T12:00:00Z"
    }
    """

    Given the file "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_document.pdf" exists in S3
    Given the file "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7851_image.jpg" exists in S3
    Given the file "019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7852_spreadsheet.xlsx" exists in S3

    When I DELETE "/api/v1/file/delete/item/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846"
    Then the response status code should be 200
    Then the response body should contain:
    """
    {
      "deletedCount": 3
    }
    """
    Then the table "files" should have 0 records
    Then the file "items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7850_document.pdf" should not exist in S3
    Then the file "items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7851_image.jpg" should not exist in S3
    Then the file "items/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7852_spreadsheet.xlsx" should not exist in S3

  Scenario: Delete files when item has no files

    When I DELETE "/api/v1/file/delete/item/019ca71b-3183-7a8b-8f71-e44a327a7846"
    Then the response status code should be 204

  Scenario: Delete files of one item does not affect files of another item

    Given the following file exists in the database:
    """
